law.text:
As used in KRS 154.12-300 to 154.12-310, unless the context indicates otherwise:
"Affiliate" means an ICC identified as the headquarters for program activity in a region or subregion;
"Commissioner" means the commissioner of the Department of Commercialization and Innovation established in KRS 154.12-278;
"ICC" means the Kentucky Innovation and Commercialization Center;
"Region" means a geographic area of Kentucky designated as having a unique innovation strategic plan by the Department of Commercialization and Innovation; and
"Satellite" means an office of an affiliate in a region.
